WEBVTT

01:29.748 --> 01:31.836
Knockdown! Knockdown!

01:31.875 --> 01:36.594
Another victory for Sweetwater!

01:38.633 --> 01:42.850
And now, for your
entertainment pleasure...

01:42.887 --> 01:44.850
while we get ready
for the main event...

01:44.890 --> 01:49.274
give it up for the Gat Boyz!

02:18.257 --> 02:21.138
I saw Louis the night
that he beat Braddock...

02:21.178 --> 02:23.974
won the title. 1937.

02:24.013 --> 02:25.934
Louis hits him
with a left and a right!

02:25.973 --> 02:27.310
And Braddock is down!

02:27.351 --> 02:29.605
Straight right hand to the jaw.

02:29.645 --> 02:31.982
Christ, they could've
counted to fifty.

02:32.022 --> 02:34.486
He was the best heavyweight...

02:34.524 --> 02:36.612
that ever fought
under the modern rules.

02:36.652 --> 02:38.822
No discussion, the best.

02:38.862 --> 02:43.246
Then the fucking government
chased him about taxes.

02:43.283 --> 02:48.168
Fucking IRS,
fucking bureaucrat assholes.

02:50.582 --> 02:52.001
Fuck it.

03:48.685 --> 03:52.233
...in the west corner,
weighing in at 230 pounds...

03:52.271 --> 03:54.484
wearing the green trunks
with the gold trim...

03:54.524 --> 03:58.406
he's undefeated with
eight wins and no losses.

03:58.444 --> 04:00.908
Representing
the State Prison at Loda...

04:00.947 --> 04:04.078
the great white hope,
Vern Van Zant!

04:07.954 --> 04:09.373
Now in the east corner...

04:09.414 --> 04:11.793
he's also undefeated
and defending champion...

04:11.833 --> 04:15.048
with a record of
67 wins and no losses...

04:15.086 --> 04:18.009
weighing in at 191 pounds...

04:18.048 --> 04:20.093
wearing the burgundy trunks
with the black trim...

04:20.132 --> 04:25.435
Sweetwater's own,
Monroe Hutchen!

04:45.034 --> 04:47.998
All right now, shit birds,
y'all both know the rules.

04:48.037 --> 04:50.960
I want a nice, clean fight,
nothing below the belt.

04:50.998 --> 04:53.754
You understand me? Let's box.

04:59.883 --> 05:01.636
Now remember,
brother convicts...

05:01.676 --> 05:03.012
if you learned how to act...

05:03.053 --> 05:04.555
they wouldn't have to fight
inside of a cage.

05:04.595 --> 05:05.974
And be on your
best behavior, too...

05:06.015 --> 05:07.768
'cause we don't want
no incidents, all right?

05:07.808 --> 05:09.144
Now, let's see what
the pride of Loda...

05:09.185 --> 05:10.980
has to offer against
the great Monroe.

05:11.019 --> 05:13.065
Give Hitler's cousin
his lunch, baby.

05:13.105 --> 05:15.485
It's all you, baby!
It's all you!

05:15.524 --> 05:17.110
Yeah! Come on now!

05:17.150 --> 05:19.029
Come back from
the rail... get back,

05:22.865 --> 05:25.203
And there go the bell.
Here we go.

05:25.243 --> 05:27.915
Monroe comes out
and peppers him...

05:27.954 --> 05:29.582
with a nice left hand,

05:29.622 --> 05:31.126
And another left hand,

05:33.834 --> 05:35.087
Monroe's
just feeling him out...

05:35.128 --> 05:37.006
popping him with
a little left hand,

05:37.045 --> 05:39.008
He going to shine that
bald head up, for sure,

05:39.048 --> 05:42.096
Move your feet!
Oh, yeah, that's right!

05:42.135 --> 05:43.930
Yeah! Yeah!

05:43.971 --> 05:45.725
Beat the teeth out of
his mouth, Monroe!

05:45.764 --> 05:46.975
Come on, man!

05:51.854 --> 05:54.860
A left and a right by Monroe!

05:54.898 --> 05:57.403
This guy hasn't
tagged Monroe yet,

05:57.443 --> 05:59.948
How in the hell
could you be 6-6, 280...

05:59.988 --> 06:01.992
and look wobbly already? Ooh!

06:02.031 --> 06:04.535
He's down! He's down!

06:04.575 --> 06:07.664
He's already down!
Vern Van Zant is down!

06:09.079 --> 06:10.750
We're not even halfway
through the first round...

06:10.790 --> 06:12.293
and he's already down!

06:12.333 --> 06:15.965
Excuse me, sir,
we just got some big news.

06:16.004 --> 06:20.054
The word is, the Iceman's
day of arrival is tomorrow.

06:20.090 --> 06:21.761
E.T.A., 2 p.m.

06:21.801 --> 06:23.805
Now, Vern Van Zant
said he got those...

06:23.845 --> 06:25.765
brand-new tattoos
just for this occasion.

06:25.804 --> 06:26.974
Well, Vern, don't look like...

06:27.016 --> 06:28.936
the parry’s gonna last
too long for you.

06:28.937 --> 06:33.192
This guy is a bum...
big, uncoordinated motherfucker.

06:33.229 --> 06:34.565
Nine...

06:36.023 --> 06:39.029
Look at me! You OK? Box!

06:40.613 --> 06:43.201
Ah, here we go again!
Monroe's on the hunt.

06:43.240 --> 06:44.910
Vern, swinging and a-missing,

06:44.951 --> 06:47.580
Ooh! And another left,
right to the midsection,

06:47.619 --> 06:49.248
Left and right
uppercuts to the head!

06:49.287 --> 06:51.208
Right to the head!
Right to the stomach,

06:51.249 --> 06:53.002
This guy's just
a-swinging and a-missing!

06:53.042 --> 06:54.544
Hits him with
a left and a right!

06:54.584 --> 06:56.505
Monroe's just
tearing his ass up,

06:56.545 --> 06:59.802
Right in the face!
Right to the head!

06:59.839 --> 07:01.885
Left to the midsection!
Right to the head!

07:01.926 --> 07:03.388
Another left and a right!

07:03.469 --> 07:04.972
Oh, my God,
he shined his head up!

07:05.012 --> 07:06.975
I told you, he's shinin' it up!

07:09.977 --> 07:11.977
One more time for Monroe,

07:11.978 --> 07:13.898
Knockout! Knockout!

07:15.606 --> 07:17.568
One round, motherfucker!

07:19.110 --> 07:21.907
That's it! That's it!

07:21.947 --> 07:27.791
It's done! This fight is over!
Monroe wins again!

07:29.621 --> 07:30.873
Spit it.

07:30.914 --> 07:32.918
Yeah, but I got a little
announcement for you.

07:32.958 --> 07:34.378
Got a little
announcement for you.

07:34.419 --> 07:35.796
Little news bulletin.

07:35.836 --> 07:37.923
Y'all been wondering
when that day is coming.

07:37.963 --> 07:41.386
Well, that day is tomorrow.
He's coming to Sweetwater.

07:41.425 --> 07:42.928
The so-called undisputed...

07:42.968 --> 07:44.930
heavyweight champion
of the world...

07:44.971 --> 07:48.603
George "Iceman" Chambers!

07:50.685 --> 07:52.564
What do you say to that,
Monroe? You ready?

08:02.906 --> 08:06.203
OK, here we go. Tape rolling.

08:07.827 --> 08:09.956
Former world
heavyweight champion...

08:09.996 --> 08:11.750
George "Iceman" Chambers...

08:11.790 --> 08:13.460
now you'll be moving
to a new home...

08:13.499 --> 08:15.670
going to live with
murderers and thieves...

08:15.710 --> 08:17.380
in California's newly-built...

08:17.421 --> 08:19.342
Sweetwater Prison
in the Mojave Desert.

08:19.381 --> 08:21.969
How's all this going for you?

08:22.008 --> 08:25.599
I'll be OK.
I got a bad break.

08:25.638 --> 08:27.558
I just gotta
play this thing out.

08:27.598 --> 08:30.771
Your lawyers have filed
all the expected appeals...

08:30.809 --> 08:33.774
but realistically, what do
you think of your chances,,,

08:33.813 --> 08:35.357
of getting out
before serving...

08:35.397 --> 08:37.903
the full sentence
of 6 to 8 years?

08:37.943 --> 08:41.698
I'm not supposed to talk
about that legal stuff.

08:41.736 --> 08:44.116
My people don't want me
commenting on that.

08:44.157 --> 08:46.119
Boxing experts tend to agree...

08:46.159 --> 08:48.664
that even as little
as two years in a prison...

08:48.744 --> 08:51.124
without proper training
could mean the end...

08:51.164 --> 08:53.377
for a boxer your age.
Now, you're regarded...

08:53.416 --> 08:55.002
as one of the greatest
offensive fighters...

08:55.043 --> 08:56.588
in the history of the sport...

08:56.628 --> 08:59.049
an attacker
like Dempsey, Joe Louis...

08:59.089 --> 09:02.053
Rocky Marciano, Joe Frazier,

09:02.092 --> 09:04.889
Just exactly how
damaging to your skills...

09:04.928 --> 09:06.890
is this prison stint
likely to be?

09:06.930 --> 09:10.645
No damage.
I'll stay in shape, work out...

09:10.684 --> 09:12.562
watch what I eat. I'll be fine.

09:12.602 --> 09:15.566
But when an athlete
is removed from competition...

09:15.606 --> 09:18.487
That's where you're making
one big mistake right off.

09:18.526 --> 09:22.951
I'm not an athlete.
I'm a gladiator.

09:22.988 --> 09:24.574
How do you define that?

09:24.615 --> 09:29.207
People play baseball.
Nobody plays boxing.

09:29.245 --> 09:32.084
Iceman, last week after
you were convicted...

09:32.123 --> 09:35.212
boxing's various
so-called governing bodies...

09:35.252 --> 09:37.172
began stripping you of
your title belts...

09:37.211 --> 09:38.589
stripping you...

09:38.629 --> 09:40.383
Who they think they kidding?

09:40.424 --> 09:42.303
Everybody knows I'm the champ.

09:42.342 --> 09:44.513
And I'm gonna be the champ
till I quit.

10:04.698 --> 10:07.621
This fight with
Manfredy is meant to be...

10:07.659 --> 10:09.622
just a tune-up for
George "The Iceman" Chambers...

10:09.661 --> 10:11.248
hopefully leading
to the unification bout...

10:11.288 --> 10:12.624
with Montel Briscoe...

10:12.665 --> 10:15.338
undefeated holder
of the WBC crown,

10:15.376 --> 10:17.964
The two biggest names in boxing
on a collision course...

10:18.004 --> 10:19.633
sometime next year...

10:19.672 --> 10:22.803
assuming the Iceman gets by
the South American challenger,

10:27.305 --> 10:30.561
It's round 1 and one to go,
and it's all Iceman!

10:30.600 --> 10:33.773
He's stalking Manfredy,
chasing the big South American,

10:38.483 --> 10:40.153
Iceman with a right,
another right,

10:40.194 --> 10:42.865
Another right
and a left to the body!

10:42.905 --> 10:46.579
Oh, and a right-hand uppercut,
That staggered Manfredy!

10:46.617 --> 10:49.748
Iceman stalking him,
He knows he's got him hurt,

10:49.787 --> 10:52.751
Oh, body shots!
Right, left to the body!

10:52.790 --> 10:55.378
Left hook and he's down!
He's down! He's down!

10:55.417 --> 10:58.090
That's why they call him
the Iceman!

10:59.712 --> 11:01.174
Well, Carlos Manfredy...

11:01.216 --> 11:03.972
gets a one-way ticket
back to Brazil!

11:05.844 --> 11:07.390
George "Iceman" Chambers...

11:07.429 --> 11:10.017
remains undefeated
heavyweight champion!

11:10.057 --> 11:12.521
And the big man on the block!

11:18.315 --> 11:20.821
Are you fighting Montel next?

11:20.902 --> 11:23.115
Just another sucker who's
gonna get his ass whipped.

11:23.154 --> 11:25.659
If the money's right,
bring on Montel.

11:25.741 --> 11:27.619
Nobody's running,
nobody's ducking.

11:27.659 --> 11:31.625
Nobody... I mean, nobody...
can stand up to what I got.

11:31.663 --> 11:33.041
Does that include Montel?

11:33.082 --> 11:35.086
Oh, yeah, that damn sure
includes Montel.

11:37.169 --> 11:38.422
Mr. Lewis!

11:38.462 --> 11:40.967
Estimates are up
to 300 million dollars...

11:41.006 --> 11:42.634
for the pay-per-view
gate alone.

11:42.675 --> 11:43.969
Any comment on that?

11:44.010 --> 11:45.638
Let's make the deal first.

11:45.678 --> 11:49.978
But my first guess is
you're a few million short.

11:50.016 --> 11:52.270
And, Iceman,
it's nine months till summer.

11:52.310 --> 11:53.645
What's next for you?

11:53.686 --> 11:55.522
Well, first of all,
I'm gonna go to L.A...

11:55.563 --> 11:57.025
you know, see some friends...

11:57.106 --> 11:58.985
then I'm gonna do
a little partying.

12:02.820 --> 12:04.490
Hey, hey...that's it.

12:04.530 --> 12:05.907
I've done things in my life...

12:05.949 --> 12:07.949
maybe I shouldn't have.
I know that.

12:07.950 --> 12:11.081
But I did not want to,
and I told him "No."

12:17.794 --> 12:20.629
You'll be moving
into a new home...

12:20.630 --> 12:22.927
going to live with
murderers and thieves...

12:23.008 --> 12:24.344
in California's newly-built...

12:24.345 --> 12:26.802
Sweetwater Prison
in the Mojave Desert,

12:26.803 --> 12:28.515
Without getting into
legal strategy...

12:28.516 --> 12:29.933
let's discuss your trial.

12:30.016 --> 12:31.644
You continue to maintain
your innocence.

12:31.725 --> 12:33.604
I didn't rape nobody.

12:33.644 --> 12:35.646
I done a lot of wrong shit
in my life...

12:35.647 --> 12:37.648
but I ain't no punk-ass rapist.

12:37.649 --> 12:40.028
Look at me.
What I gotta rape somebody for?

13:13.894 --> 13:15.438
Psst. Monroe.

13:15.479 --> 13:17.024
You see him through the window?

13:17.064 --> 13:19.110
Big deal's got his own
helicopter service...

13:19.149 --> 13:21.028
instead of coming
in here on the bus.

13:21.069 --> 13:23.156
He's the champ.

13:23.195 --> 13:26.368
What's this shit?
Don't think negative, man.

13:26.408 --> 13:27.868
I don't want to hear that shit.

13:27.908 --> 13:29.954
This is your house.
You own this place.

13:31.830 --> 13:34.209
If this was my house,
I could get up and leave.

13:44.050 --> 13:45.386
He's here.

13:45.427 --> 13:47.139
Just getting out
of the helicopter.

13:47.178 --> 13:49.976
Maybe you'd like to meet him,
Mr. Ripstein.

13:50.016 --> 13:52.145
I could bring him over.
You two could talk boxing.

13:52.183 --> 13:55.315
I'll tell you when
I want to talk to him.

14:03.487 --> 14:06.367
Why couldn't your high-priced
team of lawyers...

14:06.406 --> 14:08.368
convince a judge and a jury?

14:08.450 --> 14:10.955
Because I put people
in body bags on TV...

14:10.995 --> 14:12.915
and get paid
a lot of money for it.

14:12.955 --> 14:15.418
Because I'm a big, bad,
black motherfucker...

14:15.458 --> 14:17.253
that's why nobody believes me.

14:17.293 --> 14:20.049
I have received
over 170 requests...

14:20.088 --> 14:22.426
for interviews with you,
Mr. Chambers.

14:22.465 --> 14:24.092
Networks, local TV, cable...

14:24.133 --> 14:26.178
ever newspaper organization
in the country...

14:26.219 --> 14:29.434
foreign press, foreign TV...
you name it,

14:29.473 --> 14:31.644
I have turned them all down,

14:31.683 --> 14:35.190
Mr. Chambers,
here is Sweetwater,

14:35.227 --> 14:37.065
Maximum security, level five...

14:37.104 --> 14:38.858
state correctional
institution...

14:38.899 --> 14:41.362
with nearly
seven hundred prisoners.

14:41.401 --> 14:45.534
We house only murderers,
armed robbers, rapists...

14:45.572 --> 14:47.284
and those with
connections to gangs...

14:47.325 --> 14:49.454
and other forms
of organized crime.

14:49.493 --> 14:53.459
The state is trying to
spare lesser criminals...

14:53.497 --> 14:56.503
the contaminating influence
of these more hardened types.

14:56.541 --> 15:00.006
Now, we don't want
any incidents that might add...

15:00.045 --> 15:02.383
to your already great
difficulties, Mr. Chambers,

15:02.422 --> 15:04.426
This is Mr. Mercker.

15:04.508 --> 15:06.972
He's the senior prison officer,
He's the head guard,

15:07.011 --> 15:09.266
This is Ms. Early,
our administrative officer.

15:09.305 --> 15:10.976
She can arrange
for religious counsel...

15:11.015 --> 15:12.268
or instruction, if you wish.

15:12.308 --> 15:17.151
Whatever.
I need a CD player and some CDs.

15:17.189 --> 15:18.692
Now, I'll give you a list.

15:18.731 --> 15:20.819
My people on the outside
will pay for it all.

15:20.858 --> 15:22.654
Not possible
for the first six months.

15:22.695 --> 15:24.114
It's a privilege,
has to be earned.

15:24.153 --> 15:25.615
Any and all privileges...

15:25.697 --> 15:28.201
will depend upon
your general conduct,

15:28.241 --> 15:31.038
Mr. Chambers,
you have been convicted...

15:31.077 --> 15:32.998
and sent here
for the crime of rape.

15:33.038 --> 15:34.666
That's a very serious mater,

15:34.707 --> 15:36.251
If you'd take advantage...

15:36.291 --> 15:38.044
of this opportunity
to apologize...

15:38.085 --> 15:40.256
to this woman
and to sports fans...

15:40.296 --> 15:42.216
and the American public
for letting them down...

15:42.256 --> 15:43.925
heck, even the former
president of the...

15:43.966 --> 15:45.678
Man, fuck the president!

15:45.718 --> 15:47.012
I ain't apologizing...

15:47.051 --> 15:49.765
not to you, not to her,
not to nobody!

15:49.805 --> 15:52.101
And you lucky I got this
damn gate between you and me...

15:52.141 --> 15:55.147
or I’d rip you a new asshole,
you judgmental motherfucker!

15:56.730 --> 15:59.067
Another strong
athlete in the joint!

15:59.107 --> 16:01.654
Welcome to Sweetwater,
Chambers!

16:03.987 --> 16:05.656
If you need anything, champ...

16:05.697 --> 16:06.992
I got you covered,

16:14.748 --> 16:18.964
Hey, champ!
Seen all your fights, man!

16:28.011 --> 16:29.388
You got a name?

16:30.680 --> 16:33.394
Mingo.

16:33.433 --> 16:38.151
Mingo, move your shit,
stay out of my way...

16:38.189 --> 16:41.027
and we'll get along just fine.

16:46.530 --> 16:49.870
Hey, listen. It's an honor
to be cellmates with you.

16:49.909 --> 16:51.996
I don't want no trouble, champ.

16:52.036 --> 16:55.209
No trouble. You just gonna
stay out of my way.

16:55.247 --> 16:56.793
He just thinks he's the king.

16:56.833 --> 16:59.672
Because he's the heavyweight
champ, he's the man.

16:59.710 --> 17:01.924
Well, for some of us others,
we have rights, too...

17:01.964 --> 17:05.720
and I had the right to say no
if I didn't want to.

17:05.758 --> 17:09.223
I want everybody
to keep your distance.

17:09.304 --> 17:11.642
I don't need to make
no new friends...

17:11.682 --> 17:14.103
or hear no sad stories
on why they're here.

17:14.142 --> 17:16.439
I got my own sad story for that.

17:16.478 --> 17:18.773
I ain't loanin' nobody
no money...

17:18.814 --> 17:20.567
so you tell 'em don't even ask.

17:20.608 --> 17:22.945
And I don't want
nobody talking to me...

17:22.986 --> 17:25.531
unless I talk to 'em first.

17:25.569 --> 17:28.242
-You got that?
-Got it.

17:28.282 --> 17:30.495
"Leave the champ alone."

17:38.293 --> 17:40.755
I know boxing.

17:40.795 --> 17:43.509
I seen a lot of fights.

17:43.548 --> 17:46.887
You're a good champeen,

17:46.926 --> 17:48.429
Who the hell are you?

17:48.512 --> 17:50.307
This is Mendy Ripstein.

17:50.346 --> 17:51.975
He's a very important man
in here.

17:52.016 --> 17:53.560
Ripstein,

17:53.600 --> 17:57.984
Yeah, my manager, Yank Lewis,
he told me to say hello.

17:58.022 --> 17:59.399
I don't remember him.

17:59.439 --> 18:01.901
He said you two
were friends in Miami...

18:01.941 --> 18:03.945
about twenty-five years ago.

18:03.986 --> 18:07.201
I didn't have
any friends in Miami.

18:07.239 --> 18:10.954
A lot of people, they say
they knew me from the old days.

18:10.993 --> 18:12.663
They're full of shit.

18:12.703 --> 18:15.959
You're a good champeen...

18:15.998 --> 18:19.463
but we got a champeen
right here...

18:19.543 --> 18:22.299
and he can kick your ass.

18:25.592 --> 18:26.886
Kiddin' me.

18:26.927 --> 18:30.558
I watch all your fights.
You're not as good as you were.

18:30.597 --> 18:33.060
You're just looking
for one big punch.

18:33.099 --> 18:35.855
You're not
throwing combinations.

18:35.894 --> 18:39.693
You're not using as much
head movement on defense.

18:39.731 --> 18:40.942
Yeah, right, old man.

18:40.982 --> 18:43.278
I'm just knocking
motherfuckers out.

18:43.318 --> 18:45.782
Who's the punk in here
you got in mind?

18:45.821 --> 18:49.996
Oh, did I hurt your feelings?

18:50.033 --> 18:52.746
Fuck you.

18:58.042 --> 19:01.882
Heh. Monroe.
Name's Monroe Hutchen.

19:01.921 --> 19:04.635
Mr. Ripstein thinks
he can whip up on you, man...

19:04.674 --> 19:08.974
but no offense. Not trying
to cause any trouble here.

20:07.322 --> 20:10.077
Which one of these suckers
in here is Monroe Hutchen?

20:10.117 --> 20:14.709
He's over there in line,
wearing a white cap.

20:14.746 --> 20:16.541
What's happening, Mo? Yeah.

20:16.581 --> 20:19.003
Brought in
some big guys in here.

20:19.043 --> 20:21.922
He beat 'em all.

20:21.961 --> 20:24.508
It ain't only about being big.

20:24.548 --> 20:27.011
You gotta have skill, son.

20:38.062 --> 20:40.066
You Monroe Hutchen?

20:43.067 --> 20:44.402
Yep.

20:44.443 --> 20:48.034
I guess you know who I am.

20:48.073 --> 20:51.746
Are you the champion in here?

20:51.784 --> 20:54.163
Yeah.

20:54.203 --> 20:57.292
Not the heavyweight champ.

20:59.375 --> 21:01.546
Champion...

21:01.587 --> 21:04.175
heavyweight or
any other kind they got.

21:04.214 --> 21:09.140
I didn't even know they had
boxing in a place like this.

21:09.178 --> 21:11.808
Well, it's a special program.

21:11.846 --> 21:14.394
We only get bouts
ever six months.

21:14.433 --> 21:17.314
Mostly we fight guys
from other prisons.

21:17.353 --> 21:19.774
How long you been on top?

21:19.814 --> 21:23.530
Ten years.
Ever since I got in here.

21:23.567 --> 21:27.575
Damn. Brother, that's
a real fine record you got.

21:27.613 --> 21:30.285
I gotta congratulate you.

21:30.324 --> 21:32.705
Yeah! You want some of this?

21:32.743 --> 21:34.454
Yeah! Come on!

21:34.495 --> 21:36.332
I'm gonna win.

21:36.372 --> 21:38.501
Come on! What?

21:38.541 --> 21:41.338
Ain't no champ in here but me!

21:43.297 --> 21:46.219
I'm giving you another chance.

21:46.258 --> 21:49.138
I'm inclined to overlook
what happened this afternoon...

21:49.176 --> 21:51.180
and not make it a par of
your official record,

21:53.347 --> 21:57.147
Look, let's get something
straight, Mr. Warden.

21:57.185 --> 22:00.818
I'm not just some convict
doing five to ten.

22:00.857 --> 22:04.363
I'm a real big deal.

22:04.443 --> 22:06.697
Not only am I
heavyweight champ...

22:06.737 --> 22:09.868
I'm close to being the most
famous man in the world.

22:09.906 --> 22:11.493
So if you think
you're gonna lean on me...

22:11.534 --> 22:13.079
like these punks
you got in here...

22:13.119 --> 22:14.330
you better think again...

22:14.370 --> 22:16.458
because if anything
happens to me...

22:16.497 --> 22:20.339
it's gonna be on
the 6:00 news worldwide.

22:20.376 --> 22:22.004
There's gonna be
a whole lot of people...

22:22.045 --> 22:24.090
askin' a whole lot
of questions...

22:24.130 --> 22:26.176
and you and your little crew
here better know that.

22:26.215 --> 22:28.219
Just my luck he got sent here.

22:28.259 --> 22:31.432
Iceman, my ass.
He's just another goddamn thug.

22:31.471 --> 22:33.600
One who happens
to be a world champion...

22:33.640 --> 22:36.562
and a potential
public relations nightmare.

22:44.067 --> 22:47.114
Mr. Hutchen.

22:47.153 --> 22:48.740
You know the little problem...

22:48.781 --> 22:51.035
you had with
the Iceman yesterday?

22:51.075 --> 22:52.828
Got you in some trouble.

22:54.370 --> 22:56.792
Heavyweight champ.

22:56.831 --> 22:59.002
Man gave me a cheap shot.

22:59.041 --> 23:00.543
Yeah, I know,

23:00.584 --> 23:02.296
By the court
and the higher powers...

23:02.337 --> 23:05.176
you contributed to a situation
that threatened violence.

23:05.215 --> 23:07.761
One thing you ought
to know by now, Monroe,

23:07.800 --> 23:10.973
Life ain't fair,
Not fair at all,

23:19.353 --> 23:20.982
The warden understands...

23:21.022 --> 23:22.693
what he's doing
is unfortunate...

23:22.732 --> 23:24.987
but unless Mr. Hutchen
and the Iceman are separated...

23:25.026 --> 23:26.487
there will be
enormous pressure...

23:26.528 --> 23:28.825
for another
physical confrontation,

23:28.864 --> 23:30.325
Nobody likes this...

23:30.365 --> 23:32.327
but Mr. Hutchen's presence
is an incitement to violence...

23:32.368 --> 23:34.998
and he will be kept in there
until such time...

23:35.037 --> 23:38.627
as we can make arrangements for
his travel to another facility.

23:48.634 --> 23:50.930
OK.

23:52.555 --> 23:53.933
Hey, Monroe.

23:53.973 --> 23:55.977
Take care of yourself
in there, Monroe.

24:01.189 --> 24:01.982
Sergeant Marinez
to the hill tower,

24:01.983 --> 24:04.278
Sergeant Marinez
to the hill tower,

24:04.318 --> 24:06.822
Sergeant Marinez
to the hill tower,

24:10.573 --> 24:12.994
New duty roster just got posted.

24:13.034 --> 24:16.248
You're working
in the kitchen with me.

24:16.287 --> 24:18.959
Look, since we're gonna
be stuck together...

24:18.999 --> 24:22.714
what you in here for?

24:22.754 --> 24:24.757
You know, champ,
I don't mean to be...

24:24.796 --> 24:27.719
telling you what to do
or anything, but...

24:27.758 --> 24:32.016
it's not considered polite
to ask why we're here.

24:32.053 --> 24:35.184
Kinda violation of the ethics.
You know, the code?

24:35.224 --> 24:36.393
Yeah.

24:36.434 --> 24:39.857
People take it as disrespect.

24:39.937 --> 24:44.278
Yo! You keeping in shape,
Mr. Iceman?

24:44.317 --> 24:47.406
Who's this chump?

24:47.445 --> 24:51.161
Call him Ratbag.
Runs with Monroe.

24:51.199 --> 24:52.368
Shit.

24:52.408 --> 24:54.454
Thinks he's his manager,

24:54.494 --> 24:57.208
-Ratbag?
-Ratbag.

25:00.083 --> 25:04.509
OK, Ratbag,
what you in here for?

25:06.548 --> 25:09.345
-Me?
-Yeah, you.

25:11.595 --> 25:13.431
Arson.

25:13.471 --> 25:17.604
Nothin' up close and personal.

25:17.642 --> 25:20.064
You hit people much?

25:20.104 --> 25:21.856
What do you mean?

25:21.898 --> 25:24.111
You know, punch people.

25:24.149 --> 25:26.654
When you were a kid
or since you been in here.

25:26.694 --> 25:29.741
Sometimes. Not much.

25:29.780 --> 25:31.617
I never was the physical type.

25:31.657 --> 25:34.579
You want to hit me?

25:34.619 --> 25:38.585
What, are you kidding?

25:38.665 --> 25:40.794
You can say you did it.

25:40.834 --> 25:42.754
"I punched
the heavyweight champ."

25:42.794 --> 25:44.213
You can tell people
all about it.

25:44.253 --> 25:45.422
It might even make you...

25:45.463 --> 25:48.011
feel good about
your little punk-ass self.

25:48.049 --> 25:50.721
I don't want to hit you, Iceman.
Shit!

25:50.760 --> 25:51.929
Sure you do!

25:51.970 --> 25:53.932
You don't even like me.
Come on, man.

25:53.972 --> 25:56.311
Go crazy. Let one go.

25:56.349 --> 25:58.770
If I hit you just this once,
will that end it?

25:58.810 --> 26:00.314
I won't have to hit you anymore?

26:00.354 --> 26:02.567
All you gotta do
is hit me one time...

26:02.607 --> 26:04.986
and I'm telling you, man,
it'll make you feel good...

26:05.026 --> 26:07.656
and it ain't gonna hurt me none.

26:07.695 --> 26:09.489
Aright. Just once.

26:09.529 --> 26:11.909
Just to satisfy whatever
weird trip you're on...

26:11.949 --> 26:13.160
and show you
that I'm a good guy...

26:13.200 --> 26:14.829
trying to do what you want.

26:14.869 --> 26:16.163
Right. Thank you.

26:16.203 --> 26:18.583
You're welcome.

26:21.376 --> 26:22.503
Unh!

26:22.543 --> 26:24.129
Ohh! Yeah, baby!

26:24.171 --> 26:27.969
Oh, yeah! Yeah!
I hit the Iceman!

26:28.007 --> 26:29.176
Yo!

26:30.509 --> 26:34.058
-Yeah!
-Thank you.

26:34.096 --> 26:35.933
You still feel good, Ratbag?

26:35.973 --> 26:38.311
Yeah. I guess so.

26:38.351 --> 26:40.271
You're not mad, are you?

26:40.312 --> 26:42.107
Ohh! Damn!

26:42.147 --> 26:44.026
No, I'm not mad at you.

26:44.066 --> 26:47.030
Now, you go tell Monroe
what I said.

26:47.069 --> 26:49.030
Ain't but one champ in here!

26:49.071 --> 26:51.700
And it ain't some
nickel-and-dime convict...

26:51.740 --> 26:53.702
beating up on fools in prison!

26:53.742 --> 26:55.913
Get that bitch outta here.

27:33.117 --> 27:35.789
I ain't gotta spend my time
makin' potato salad.

27:37.370 --> 27:38.580
Where I come from...

27:38.621 --> 27:41.002
we didn't have
any kind of salads.

27:41.041 --> 27:43.337
Where's that?

27:43.377 --> 27:46.842
Indian country. Oklahoma.

27:46.880 --> 27:49.010
Hmm.

27:49.049 --> 27:50.594
Look, man, I know
I'm not supposed to ask...

27:50.635 --> 27:52.389
but what you in here for?

27:54.888 --> 27:57.351
I stole some rich guy's
Mercedes in L.A.

27:59.560 --> 28:02.734
I got a Mercedes. Three of 'em.

28:05.984 --> 28:07.737
Mr. Hutchen.

28:07.776 --> 28:10.907
It's Darlene Early, the G.A.O.
General administration officer.

28:10.946 --> 28:14.829
I need to do
the interview and paperwork...

28:14.868 --> 28:16.705
for your transfer to Folsom.

28:16.745 --> 28:19.959
How are your spirits?
I want you to know...

28:19.998 --> 28:21.668
I'm not in favor
of solitary confinement.

28:21.708 --> 28:24.505
Not for you,
not for anybody else.

28:24.545 --> 28:26.548
It's OK in here.

28:26.589 --> 28:28.091
You can't be serious.

28:28.174 --> 28:31.347
It's all a prison.

28:31.384 --> 28:33.848
I live inside my head.

28:33.888 --> 28:36.643
So that's how
you're doing your time?

28:36.681 --> 28:39.979
Are you really that much
in control of your emotions?

28:42.020 --> 28:45.109
Been that way all my life.

28:45.148 --> 28:48.989
Only time I ever lost it
is what got me in here.

28:49.028 --> 28:53.119
Yeah. I'm familiar
with your case history.

28:53.157 --> 28:56.330
So you prefer your own company?

28:56.369 --> 28:58.373
Most of the time.

28:58.412 --> 29:00.834
I am supposed to recommend
whether or not...

29:00.874 --> 29:03.964
you seem to require a detailed
psychiatric evaluation.

29:04.002 --> 29:05.838
Other than the incident
in the mess hall...

29:05.879 --> 29:07.508
That wasn't me.

29:07.547 --> 29:10.971
Why don't you
go talk to the hotshot champ?

29:11.009 --> 29:12.638
Ask him about it.

29:12.678 --> 29:14.974
So you deny any responsibility?

29:15.013 --> 29:18.521
Yeah, I deny it. How does
that affect me movin' on?

29:18.559 --> 29:21.899
This has no bearing
in your transfer to Folsom.

29:25.023 --> 29:26.986
You know, this whole thing...

29:27.026 --> 29:30.241
this whole thing
is about people bein' scared.

29:30.279 --> 29:32.491
Aren't you afraid of him?

29:32.532 --> 29:35.621
Afraid. Shit, no.

29:35.659 --> 29:37.246
He's a fighter. I'm a fighter.

29:37.287 --> 29:38.956
If I'm better on that day,
I win.

29:38.996 --> 29:40.499
That's just the way it goes.

29:40.581 --> 29:45.215
Someday, ever fighter loses.

29:45.253 --> 29:46.965
Sooner or later,
somebody comes along...

29:47.005 --> 29:49.677
and they got your ticket.

29:49.716 --> 29:54.266
Too old, just wasn't your day,
whatever the reason is.

29:54.305 --> 29:58.062
In the end,
everybody gets beaten.

29:59.560 --> 30:04.194
The most you can hope for
is that you stay on top a while.

30:04.231 --> 30:05.775
Be the best.

30:10.654 --> 30:13.034
I tried to say hello
to that old gangster.

30:13.073 --> 30:15.662
Ripstein.
He said he don't remember you.

30:15.702 --> 30:18.916
He remembers.
He just don't want to admit it.

30:18.954 --> 30:21.042
Standard mob procedure.

30:21.082 --> 30:23.253
Guys like him deny
they ever had a mother.

30:23.293 --> 30:25.589
Yeah. Right.

30:25.628 --> 30:28.216
How you makin' out, man?

30:28.256 --> 30:30.594
It's shit, but I can handle it.

30:30.634 --> 30:33.013
Yeah. Rumor goin' around
you almost stared a riot.

30:33.052 --> 30:35.056
It was all bullshit, man.

30:35.095 --> 30:37.851
I had to let the peeps in here
know who's the boss.

30:37.891 --> 30:40.062
Just keep
your goddamn nose clean.

30:40.101 --> 30:42.022
You already got
enough problems.

30:43.188 --> 30:45.317
And since they stripped
you of your title...

30:45.357 --> 30:47.361
they're having this
elimination tournament...

30:47.400 --> 30:48.820
to figure out a new champ.

30:48.860 --> 30:52.780
Everybody thinks
Briscoe's a lock to win it.

30:52.781 --> 30:55.745
Word is, Montel's fighting
Jimmy Stubbs in July.

30:55.785 --> 30:57.622
Jimmy Stubbs's a bum.

30:57.661 --> 31:00.458
The good news is
you get outta here...

31:00.498 --> 31:02.961
fight the new champ,
we're looking at...

31:03.000 --> 31:04.796
the biggest payday
of boxing history.

31:04.834 --> 31:07.005
-Mm-hmm.
-Yeah.

31:07.045 --> 31:10.093
The one thing I can tell you,
you lost a lot of fan base...

31:10.174 --> 31:12.303
with this conviction thing.

31:12.343 --> 31:14.222
Fuck the fans.

31:14.261 --> 31:16.934
I get outta here,
I'll get 'em back.

31:16.974 --> 31:22.025
The fans pay your bills,
and don't you ever forget it.

31:22.062 --> 31:24.813
Yeah.

31:24.814 --> 31:26.818
You gotta keep the pressure
on these lawyers, OK...

31:26.857 --> 31:28.194
and get you outta here
to fight this...

31:28.235 --> 31:29.988
big money fight with Briscoe.

31:30.027 --> 31:31.196
Yeah.

31:31.239 --> 31:33.785
You can't be servin'
no full sentence.

31:33.824 --> 31:36.036
You're 35 years old.
Time is tickin'.

31:36.076 --> 31:38.372
Everything
you ever worked for...

31:38.412 --> 31:40.082
it's going
right out the window.

31:43.292 --> 31:44.837
Janiro's an agile boxer...

31:44.876 --> 31:46.421
who has the ability
of a champion,

31:46.461 --> 31:48.048
Janiro is fresh off a victor...

31:48.088 --> 31:50.050
over Charlie Consario,

31:50.090 --> 31:51.634
The Rock turns it on,

31:51.675 --> 31:53.137
It's Le Graziano alone,

31:53.177 --> 31:55.055
He won't give Janiro
punching room,

31:55.095 --> 31:56.348
Stays after his man,

31:56.389 --> 31:59.060
Hits him from all angles,

31:59.099 --> 32:00.602
He remembers things
from a long time ago...

32:00.643 --> 32:02.104
clear as a bell...

32:02.145 --> 32:04.608
but ever day,
I gotta tell him who I am.

32:04.647 --> 32:09.031
He's in another world:
Cuba, forty years ago...

32:09.068 --> 32:11.531
or some fight he saw in 1953.

32:11.571 --> 32:13.116
Then all of a sudden...

32:13.156 --> 32:16.329
he's right there with you,
like everything's normal.

32:16.368 --> 32:18.831
And mean...
he can be mean as shit.

32:18.870 --> 32:21.167
Look, we went to the Emme.

32:21.206 --> 32:23.043
We paid good money
for his protection...

32:23.082 --> 32:24.502
and his personal needs.

32:24.543 --> 32:26.380
They gave you the job.

32:26.420 --> 32:28.214
I got him an oversized cell...

32:28.254 --> 32:31.344
ground level, so he don't
have to use the stairs.

32:31.382 --> 32:35.057
Food privileges.
Relaxed dress code.

32:35.095 --> 32:36.556
Big easy chair.

32:36.597 --> 32:38.726
I even got him his own
little boxing library.

32:38.766 --> 32:41.980
And he's safe. I promise.

32:42.019 --> 32:44.732
These guys I got, they don't
let any harm come his way.

33:09.840 --> 33:11.051
Hey, chief.

33:12.175 --> 33:13.386
Mmm.

33:14.552 --> 33:17.308
How you getting along
with your new cellmate?

33:17.348 --> 33:20.646
-He's OK.
-Mmm.

33:20.685 --> 33:24.024
Rumor has it he took down
one of the skinheads.

33:25.648 --> 33:29.906
A lot of rumors in prison,
you know?

33:29.944 --> 33:32.825
Ah, probably deserved it anyway.

33:32.863 --> 33:34.449
Maybe.

33:43.708 --> 33:46.213
We hear you don't want to
associate with anybody here.

33:46.252 --> 33:49.633
Maybe you got
way too much attitude, man.

33:59.182 --> 34:00.978
Unh.

34:02.560 --> 34:04.982
Aaron's an expert.
He's the man on appeals.

34:05.022 --> 34:07.067
But before we talk
about your appeal...

34:07.108 --> 34:09.989
I need to tell you about
Miss Tawnee Rawlins.

34:10.027 --> 34:13.408
She's filed a civil lawsuit
in the amount of $75 million.

34:13.447 --> 34:16.578
You handlin' that?

34:16.618 --> 34:19.331
I'd recommend
an outside attorney.

34:19.370 --> 34:20.539
Another specialist.

34:20.580 --> 34:23.460
However, we can handle
your tax litigation.

34:23.498 --> 34:25.837
The government has filed
an intent to audit.

34:25.877 --> 34:27.839
We have someone in the firm
that can deal with that.

34:27.879 --> 34:29.005
Is any of this covered...

34:29.047 --> 34:31.384
by the $2 million
I already paid you?

34:31.424 --> 34:33.594
We get the same deal as you get.

34:33.635 --> 34:37.059
You get paid win or lose.
So do we.

34:37.096 --> 34:39.434
There are a couple
of procedural areas...

34:39.475 --> 34:42.606
that are still in question...
possible reversible error.

34:42.643 --> 34:46.025
But I'm not gonna kid you.
I'd make us a long shot.

34:46.063 --> 34:48.150
You're looking at
a six- to eight-year sentence...

34:48.190 --> 34:50.696
with possible time off
for good behavior.

34:50.735 --> 34:52.531
Now, in California,
that means...

34:52.571 --> 34:55.744
you're eligible for parole
in four years.

34:55.783 --> 34:56.952
What you need to focus on...

34:56.992 --> 34:58.829
is if you become
a model prisoner...

34:58.869 --> 35:00.957
exhibit
special circumstances...

35:00.997 --> 35:02.960
you could be considered
for a work furlough...

35:02.999 --> 35:04.877
as soon as eighteen months
to two years.

35:07.044 --> 35:09.256
So it don't matter
whether I did it or not?

35:09.296 --> 35:10.465
It doesn't work that way.

35:10.506 --> 35:12.217
Justice and the law
are separate issues.

35:12.218 --> 35:14.930
Let's get back to
some of your other problems.

35:14.969 --> 35:16.179
We've done an audit.

35:16.220 --> 35:18.642
Your financial situation
is a mess.

35:18.682 --> 35:20.518
-No, that's bullshit.
-No bullshit.

35:20.558 --> 35:24.399
Big financial settlements
with your ex-wives, entourage.

35:24.437 --> 35:26.191
Bad investments
and misrepresentations...

35:26.231 --> 35:27.692
by your ex-business manager.

35:27.732 --> 35:29.111
I'm gonna sue that motherfucker.

35:29.150 --> 35:33.033
And what about this IRS shit?
Where do I stand on that?

35:33.072 --> 35:36.537
By the firm's calculations,
you could end up owing them...

35:36.574 --> 35:39.914
$7 million in back taxes,
and that's just the feds.

35:39.953 --> 35:42.625
Then there's the state.
The bottom line...

35:42.665 --> 35:44.919
we need to get
your black ass outta here...

35:44.958 --> 35:46.335
and back in the ring.

36:05.314 --> 36:07.025
Clive Johnson here ringside...

36:07.064 --> 36:09.110
for KHIL Channel 13
in the Bay Area,

36:09.150 --> 36:11.780
Next, round seven
of the California...

36:11.861 --> 36:13.573
state heavyweight
championship fight...

36:13.613 --> 36:18.414
here from the Palmer Arena
in downtown Oakland,

36:18.452 --> 36:20.039
Challenger Monroe Hutchen's
undefeated...

36:20.078 --> 36:21.874
takin' on
state champ Butch Davis...

36:21.913 --> 36:24.043
in what, so far,
has been a nearly even fight,

36:24.082 --> 36:25.791
There's the bell!

36:25.792 --> 36:27.755
Davis has a bad cut
above his left eye...

36:27.793 --> 36:29.005
and Monroe Hutchen
looks like...

36:29.047 --> 36:31.092
he wants to do
something about it,

36:32.674 --> 36:35.095
It's all Monroe,
it's all Monroe!

36:36.346 --> 36:38.642
A big right hand,
Another right!

36:38.680 --> 36:42.020
Davis is down,
and this fight is over!

36:42.059 --> 36:45.065
After forty-three seconds
in the seventh round...

36:45.104 --> 36:46.858
Monroe Hutchen is the new...

36:46.898 --> 36:49.027
California state
heavyweight champion!

36:55.114 --> 36:56.950
Your attorneys have
come to me and asked me...

36:56.990 --> 36:59.245
to handle your response
to the plaintiff's filing,

36:59.286 --> 37:02.709
As you know, you are now facing
a separate civil suit...

37:02.747 --> 37:04.166
that may well go to trial...

37:04.207 --> 37:06.963
over the criminal charges
