You're killing him!

43:41.617 --> 43:44.665
On the night
of December 1, 1990...

43:44.705 --> 43:47.623
you beat a man to death
with your bare fists...

43:47.624 --> 43:49.586
which because
of your profession...

43:49.626 --> 43:51.088
and your training
are considered...

43:51.128 --> 43:54.175
to be lethal weapons
in the state of California,

43:54.214 --> 43:56.593
You've been found guilty
by a jury of your peers...

43:56.633 --> 43:58.387
and you are sentenced
to life imprisonment...

43:58.428 --> 44:01.141
without the possibility of parole,

44:08.771 --> 44:11.318
Good morning, Mr. Ripstein.
How are you today?

44:11.357 --> 44:12.944
Don't give me no shit.

44:12.984 --> 44:14.528
How the hell
is the fight comin'?

44:14.569 --> 44:16.072
What fight?

44:16.112 --> 44:19.118
We got the heavyweight
champion of the world...

44:19.158 --> 44:21.746
and an unbeaten prospect
right here in Sweetwater.

44:21.784 --> 44:24.790
Quit wasting time.
Set the fuckin' thing up.

44:24.829 --> 44:26.163
I know fights.

44:26.164 --> 44:29.755
Long prize,
Monroe kicks his ass...

44:29.793 --> 44:31.797
we can make
a lot of money here.

44:33.255 --> 44:37.175
Mr. Ripstein, excuse me,
but you're talking about...

44:37.176 --> 44:40.178
the real heavyweight
champion of the world.

44:40.179 --> 44:42.180
Are you gonna fix the fight?

44:42.181 --> 44:43.767
Shit no. Boxing.

44:43.807 --> 44:47.106
It's a matter of style.
They all can be beaten.

44:47.145 --> 44:50.777
Right time, right place,
the right circumstance...

44:50.814 --> 44:53.862
they all can be beaten.

44:55.861 --> 44:58.115
Mr. Ripstein wants
to see the Iceman...

44:58.156 --> 45:00.118
fight a prisoner
we got in here.

45:00.158 --> 45:02.120
His name is Monroe Hutchen.

45:02.160 --> 45:05.668
And a real goddamn fight. Pure.

45:05.706 --> 45:08.461
So, what do you want us to do?

45:08.500 --> 45:11.631
I talked to the head guard.
He's OK.

45:11.670 --> 45:13.131
But the warden's a problem.

45:13.171 --> 45:15.342
Mr. Ripstein said
you can take care of him.

45:15.382 --> 45:18.550
You know the drill.

45:18.551 --> 45:22.225
You help him or you hurt him.

45:23.391 --> 45:26.229
Now...about Monroe Hutchen.

45:27.561 --> 45:29.147
The warden thinks it's time...

45:29.188 --> 45:31.150
to give him a chance
to rehabilitate himself...

45:31.189 --> 45:33.778
by socializing
with the other prisoners.

45:33.818 --> 45:36.155
In six weeks,
I'm going on vacation.

45:36.195 --> 45:37.698
On the fifth,
I'll be gone for two weeks.

45:37.738 --> 45:39.283
First week in New Orleans...

45:39.323 --> 45:42.371
second week visiting
friends in Tucson, Arizona.

45:42.410 --> 45:43.745
If while I am gone...

45:43.786 --> 45:46.580
if Mr. Hutchen happens to
get into a sparring match...

45:46.581 --> 45:49.169
with Mr. Chambers,
I don't want to hear about it.

45:49.208 --> 45:50.584
And when I get back...

45:50.585 --> 45:53.758
I want this whole goddamned
enterprise finished.

45:53.797 --> 45:54.966
Yes, sir.

45:55.006 --> 45:56.759
Leaving no evidence,
no videotape...

45:56.800 --> 45:59.305
and never to be
spoken of in my presence.

45:59.344 --> 46:00.931
-Anything else, sir?
-Hit the yard.

46:00.971 --> 46:02.223
Thank you.

46:05.100 --> 46:06.937
Had to have been somebody
in the governor's office.

46:06.938 --> 46:08.104
Soon as he got the call...

46:08.146 --> 46:09.940
Mr. Backbone stared
arranging his vacation.

46:09.941 --> 46:11.108
Know what that means,
don't you?

46:11.148 --> 46:13.319
This whole load of shit
